flavor_text_entries.diamond:
It ensnares prey by extending
arms made of vines. Losing arms to
predators does not trouble it.
flavor_text_entries.pearl:
It ensnares prey by extending
arms made of vines. Losing arms to
predators does not trouble it.
flavor_text_entries.platinum:
Its arms are made of plants that
bind themselves to things. They
grow back right away if cut.
flavor_text_entries.heartgold:
When it remains still, it appears to be a
large shrub. Unsuspecting prey that
wander near get ensnared by its vines.
flavor_text_entries.soulsilver:
Its vines grow so profusely that, in the
warm season, you can’t even see
its eyes.
flavor_text_entries.black:

bind themselves to things. They
grow back right away if cut.
flavor_text_entries.white:

flavor_text_entries.black-2:
Even if one of its arms is eaten,
it’s fine. The Pokémon regenerates
quickly and will go right back to normal.

flavor_text_entries.sword:
Tangrowth has two arms that it can extend as it
pleases. Recent research has shown that these
arms are, in fact, bundles of vines.
flavor_text_entries.shield:
Vine growth is accelerated for Tangrowth living in
warm climates. If the vines grow long, Tangrowth
shortens them by tearing parts of them off.
flavor_text_entries.legends-arceus:
Draped with long vines, it resembles a shrub in appearance.
It swings bundles of vines as though they were arms, wrapping
them around prey to ensnare them.
